                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> Itaka doesn't have a creature @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Grabbed] in its jaws</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> Itaka draws breath into its powerful lungs to drag prey into its maw. Each creature in a @Template[cone|distance:15] must succeed at a @Check[fortitude|dc:18] save or be pulled up to 10 feet closer to Itaka. Creatures that fail take @Damage[1d12[bludgeoning]] damage from the sudden pressure change. If at least one creature ends this forced movement adjacent to Itaka, Itaka can make a jaws Strike against that creature. If this Strike is a critical success, the creature is also grabbed in Itaka's jaws.</p>"
                },
